## Mandatory Execution Rules

### TDG Rules (MUST FOLLOW)
1. **Test First**: Every fix must have a test written BEFORE implementation
2. **Minimal Implementation**: Only write code to make the test pass
3. **Refactor After Green**: Improve code only after tests pass
4. **Document Coverage**: Every public function needs a test
5. **No Test, No Merge**: Untested code cannot be committed

### STAMP Rules (MUST FOLLOW)
1. **Safety Constraints**: All 5 safety constraints must be verified
2. **STPA Before Features**: Hazard analysis before new test categories
3. **CAST After Failures**: Every test failure gets causal analysis
4. **Control Structure**: Maintain clear test execution control flow
5. **Systemic Thinking**: Consider test suite as integrated system

### Execution Checkpoints
1. **CP1**: API documentation complete (4.1.1)
2. **CP2**: Base test cases fixed (4.1.3)
3. **CP3**: Core domains passing (4.2.4)
4. **CP4**: Integration tests passing (4.3.4)
5. **CP5**: Full suite green (4.4.4)

